Tom Peterson is the president of Catholics Come Home, the apostolate which produces those gorgeous television ads that have helped numerous souls return to the Catholic faith. He regularly speaks at Catholic conferences and pro-life events throughout the world, and has presented at the Vatican and the United States Conference of Catholic Bishops. He has also been featured on EWTN, Fox News, and Catholic radio stations throughout the country. 

We spent fifteen years searching for the perfect talk on modern evangelization and we finally found it. You'll never forget Tom Peterson's experience with a flight attendant or what happened on the ex-con's fishing trip. Tom's own story about how he changed his outlook on life is truly inspirational.

This talk is must-listening for practicing and non-practicing Catholics alike.

